# diameter

- _diameter(g)_

Answer the diameter of the geometry _g_,
which is twice the `radius`.

At `Circle`:

```
>>> Circle([0 0], 1).diameter
2
```

At `Sphere`:

```
>>> Sphere([0 0 0], 1).diameter
2
```

